&lt;p&gt;This specimen exudes a kind of care and individualism that you don&amp;rsquo;t normally see. The &amp;ldquo;Glorette&amp;rdquo; brand was pioneered by a man named Harry Virgil Glore, and was &lt;a href="https://patents.google.com/patent/US2040480A/en?q=%28glore%29&amp;amp;inventor=harry&amp;#43;v&amp;amp;oq=harry&amp;#43;v&amp;#43;glore"&gt;patented&lt;/a&gt; in 1933 and produced (as far as I&amp;rsquo;m able to tell) for only a few years. There was no model 2.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>